item.title: Jni
item.dc:creator: @BobDole81 BobDole81
item.description:
@BobDole81 wrote:

The only difference between using a static vs non-static native method is that the class is referenced in the c code instead of the class’s calling instance. If you use the javah utility and just copy-paste the function header, you should have no problems with that.

Does the error still occur if you don’t have a native main method (there shouldn’t be an issue even if main is native)

Read full topic
